busdesc: Jefferies Financial Group Inc., a diversified financial services company, engages in investment banking and capital markets, asset management, and direct investing businesses in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia.

As of November 3, 2009, Schering-Plough Corporation was acquired by Merck & Co. Inc. Schering-Plough Corporation discovers, develops, manufactures, and sells pharmaceuticals worldwide. It operates in three segments: Prescription Pharmaceuticals, Animal Health, and Consumer Health Care.

The ODP Corporation provides business services and supplies, products, and technology solutions for small, medium, and enterprise businesses. The company operates in three divisions: Business Solutions, Retail, and CompuCom.

Marriott International, Inc. operates, franchises, and licenses hotel, residential, and timeshare properties worldwide. The company operates through North American Full-Service, North American Limited-Service, and Asia Pacific segments.
ConocoPhillips explores for, produces, transports, and markets crude oil, bitumen, natural gas, liquefied natural gas (LNG), and natural gas liquids worldwide.

Parker-Hannifin Corporation manufactures and sells motion and control technologies and systems for various mobile, industrial, and aerospace markets worldwide. The company operates through two segments, Diversified Industrial and Aerospace Systems.
The Estee Lauder Companies Inc. manufactures and markets skin care, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products worldwide.

As of September 2, 2016, Tyco International plc was acquired by Johnson Controls International plc. Tyco International plc provides security products and services, fire detection and suppression products and services, and life safety products worldwide.
Invesco Ltd. is a publicly owned investment manager.

As of September 30, 2020, the Company owned or held a direct or indirect ownership interest in 294 apartment communities containing 86,676 apartment homes in 11 states and the District of Columbia, of which 19 communities were under development and one community was under redevelopment.
Seagate Technology plc provides data storage technology and solutions in Singapore, the United States, the Netherlands, and internationally.
Roper Technologies, Inc. designs and develops software, and engineered products and solutions worldwide.
FedEx Corporation provides transportation, e-commerce, and business services worldwide. Its FedEx Express segment offers shipping services for delivery of packages and freight.

NVR, Inc. operates as a homebuilder in the United States. The company operates in two segments, Homebuilding and Mortgage Banking. It primarily constructs and sells single-family detached homes, townhomes, and condominium buildings under the Ryan Homes, NVHomes, and Heartland Homes names.
CVS Health Corporation provides health services and plans in the United States.
Nielsen Holdings plc, together with its subsidiaries, operates as a measurement and data analytics company worldwide. It operates in two segments, Connect and Media.
